                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.48 Earthquake of 1931/85: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName> [<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1931-04-06T17:19:00-05:00"
                            notBefore="1931-04-05T15:00:00-05:45">undated</date>].<lb/>[Received
                        April 6, 1931—5:19 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Supplementing my [April] 5th, 2 p.m. Sanitation of Managua is under control of a
                    committee composed of two Nicaraguan doctors and the medical director of the
                    Guardia Nacional, Commander Gordon Hale, Medical Corps, United States Navy. They
                    have divided the city into four districts each under one or more Nicaraguan
                    doctors. Red Cross units from the other Central American countries are giving
                    the committee active aid. All persons are being inoculated against typhoid.
                    General health conditions remain good. All hospital patients are under tentage
                    on La Loma Field. No serious illness here among Americans. More than 650 dead
                    have been buried to date. The work of recovering the dead continues but it is
                    probable that hundreds will never be recovered.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
